I gave Chupacabra a shot within a week after starting my new job within its vicinity. I had only heard from a friend that it was 'supposed' to be good. I decided to venture over for a brief 30 minute lunch. I was in the mood for something small so I got the Yuca con Chicharones.  There's about 4 picnic-sized tables to the side of the restaurant. When you walk in it's a somewhat cozy waiting area with a clean, open kitchen where you can hear work being done; I always think it's weird when you go into a take out restaurant and can't hear anything being done in the kitchen.  I'm sure they're known for their tacos, but I couldn't make a decision, so I decided to go with the above appetizer. The yuca was thick and soft to the bite, but not too soft. The pork medallions (along with the yuca) were fried perfectly. The pork was fatty and flavorful. They offered two sauces on the front counter, a habanero sauce and salsa de verde. The salsa de verde is not your traditional peruvian chicken green sauce, it was more liquidy and just a little sweet with a hint of spice. The habanero sauce was obviously more spicy with a similar consistency to its green counterpart. I personally liked the habanero better, it's definitely not the kind of sauce where they don't encourage you to use it, but rather be liberal with it.  The service was good, the woman who took my order was friendly and asked me how it was after I reup'd on sauce. The kitchen staff greeted me as well, which is always a welcoming gesture.  I think a rating of 'Very Good' is an accurate statement for my first visit to Chupacabra. I will definitely go back to try out their tacos, sopa de res, and cubano, to name a few desirables.  You had me at hello, Chupacabra.

Not off to a great start at the H St location. Tried stopping by on Thursday night for the soft opening....arrived at 8:59pm and was turned down at the door with a dismissive "We're closed - come back tomorrow." Tried again on Sunday - two days after the official opening - and was greeted by a closed restaurant with no hours posted.  We live locally and have been eagerly awaiting this opening, but we've been sorely disappointed by the poor customer service and lack of community IQ. We were more than ready to make Chupacabra our go-to local spot a few times a week, but the oh-for-two experience so far has definitely turned us off.
